- Joining us first on CNBC to react,

01:00:36.190 --> 01:00:37.490
the man in question Bill Browder,

01:00:37.490 --> 01:00:39.650
Hermitage Capital Management.

01:00:39.650 --> 01:00:41.710
Bill, good to have you here,
I bet you're not surprised

01:00:41.710 --> 01:00:44.550
to hear Vladimir Putin
refer to you directly.

01:00:44.550 --> 01:00:46.930
- It's not the first time and
it won't be the last time.

01:00:46.930 --> 01:00:49.620
Vladimir Putin is very mad at me.

01:00:49.620 --> 01:00:52.740
He's mad at me because
of the Magnitsky Act.

01:00:52.740 --> 01:00:55.010
The Magnitsky Act is
a piece of legislation

01:00:55.010 --> 01:00:57.760
named after my murdered
lawyer Sergei Magnitsky.

01:00:57.760 --> 01:01:01.800
He was murdered after
uncovering a $230 million

01:01:01.800 --> 01:01:03.540
Russian corruption scandal.

01:01:03.540 --> 01:01:07.520
Some of that $230 million went
to Vladimir Putin himself.

01:01:07.520 --> 01:01:11.450
And so Putin feels personally exposed

01:01:11.450 --> 01:01:14.100
and potentially at risk
of having his assets

01:01:14.100 --> 01:01:16.840
seized in the West, and
so every chance he gets

01:01:16.840 --> 01:01:21.630
he tries to get foreign
countries to come after me.

01:01:21.630 --> 01:01:24.240
This is just one of many of his attempts.

01:01:24.240 --> 01:01:26.730
- He leveled an accusation
at you, that you funneled,

01:01:26.730 --> 01:01:30.380
and helped funnel lots of money
to Hillary Clinton, did you?

01:01:30.380 --> 01:01:31.570
- I did not.

01:01:31.570 --> 01:01:33.540
I did not, I'm not a US citizen,

01:01:33.540 --> 01:01:34.660
I don't live in the United States,

01:01:34.660 --> 01:01:36.870
I've been living in Britain for 29 years.

01:01:36.870 --> 01:01:40.003
I make no campaign contributions.

01:01:41.250 --> 01:01:43.730
And so that's not true,
I should also point out

01:01:43.730 --> 01:01:46.360
that Vladimir Putin and his regime

01:01:46.360 --> 01:01:48.260
have accused me of serial killing,

01:01:48.260 --> 01:01:50.930
of being a CIA, MI6 agent,

01:01:50.930 --> 01:01:54.150
and about a thousand other
things, and so they just kind of,

01:01:54.150 --> 01:01:57.210
he's kind of unhinged
in these accusations.

01:01:57.210 --> 01:01:59.780
- You said before, Bill, that
this is not the first time

01:01:59.780 --> 01:02:03.640
that President Putin has
mentioned you, has called you out.

01:02:03.640 --> 01:02:06.570
What is your reaction in terms
of your personal security

01:02:06.570 --> 01:02:08.950
after such a news conference,
do you increase it,

01:02:08.950 --> 01:02:11.520
do you look behind you when
you're walking down the street

01:02:11.520 --> 01:02:13.310
a little bit more often?

01:02:13.310 --> 01:02:16.430
- Well my personal
security has been at risk

01:02:16.430 --> 01:02:17.710
for a very long time.

01:02:17.710 --> 01:02:21.150
This is not, this struggle
that I'm having with Putin

01:02:21.150 --> 01:02:22.980
has been going on for 10 years.

01:02:22.980 --> 01:02:26.760
I mean, just a month ago
on May 30th in Madrid,

01:02:26.760 --> 01:02:30.040
I was arrested on a Russian
Interpol arrest warrant

01:02:30.040 --> 01:02:31.453
by the Spanish police.

01:02:32.510 --> 01:02:35.620
Thankfully I was, Interpol
contacted them two hours

01:02:35.620 --> 01:02:38.320
after I was arrested and
made sure I was released,

01:02:38.320 --> 01:02:41.100
but the Russians have been
coming after me for a long time

01:02:41.100 --> 01:02:43.680
and so I'm not surprised,
it doesn't change anything.

01:02:43.680 --> 01:02:46.250
I'm always on high alert.

01:02:46.250 --> 01:02:47.840
And there's a lot of
people around the world,

01:02:47.840 --> 01:02:50.393
governments, people, who
are looking after me.

01:02:51.660 --> 01:02:55.180
- So what had happened
with Browder was that

01:02:55.180 --> 01:02:59.070
he believed in these early
years of the Putin regime,

01:02:59.070 --> 01:03:03.080
he believed that it was
all due to his own acumen

01:03:03.080 --> 01:03:08.080
as an investor and his status as,

01:03:08.220 --> 01:03:10.950
at that time he was a US citizen,

01:03:10.950 --> 01:03:15.020
that he was able to go
after these oligarchs.

01:03:15.020 --> 01:03:18.540
What he didn't understand,
and that he learned later,

01:03:18.540 --> 01:03:21.540
was that he was pushing
against an open door

01:03:21.540 --> 01:03:25.060
because he was going
after Yeltsin's oligarchs

01:03:26.262 --> 01:03:29.290
which Putin also wanted to get rid of.

01:03:29.290 --> 01:03:33.740
But once he started going
after Putin's oligarchs

01:03:33.740 --> 01:03:35.710
he ran into a brick wall.

01:03:35.710 --> 01:03:39.530
His accountant and lawyer, Magnitsky,

01:03:39.530 --> 01:03:43.600
was killed by the Russian police

01:03:43.600 --> 01:03:48.550
in a horrific scheme that's
described at great length

01:03:48.550 --> 01:03:50.163
in his book "Red Notice"

01:03:51.200 --> 01:03:53.070
and he then went on this crusade

01:03:53.070 --> 01:03:55.020
to get the Magnitsky Act passed,

01:03:55.020 --> 01:03:58.806
which enables the US
government to seize the assets

01:03:58.806 --> 01:04:02.040
of oligarchs who are involved
in illegal activities,

01:04:02.040 --> 01:04:04.703
and which was used after,

01:04:05.690 --> 01:04:07.880
after the invasion of

01:04:09.120 --> 01:04:11.050
Ukraine in 2014.

01:04:11.050 --> 01:04:13.390
And that's what the famous 2016

01:04:13.390 --> 01:04:15.370
Trump Tower meeting was about,

01:04:15.370 --> 01:04:19.740
that the Putin regime was trying to get

01:04:19.740 --> 01:04:24.700
Trump to promise that they
would repeal the Magnitsky Act.

01:04:24.700 --> 01:04:28.803
And so that saga is ongoing.

01:04:30.790 --> 01:04:35.450
So Russia, one of the most
corrupt countries in the world,

01:04:35.450 --> 01:04:40.450
you can see here it's up there
with countries like Nigeria.

01:04:40.770 --> 01:04:45.600
This is one standard measure of corruption

01:04:45.600 --> 01:04:48.313
from Transparency International.

01:04:49.580 --> 01:04:52.260
You can see this is

01:04:52.260 --> 01:04:55.630
subjective perceptions of corruption

01:04:55.630 --> 01:04:57.303
in Russia that people think,

01:04:58.370 --> 01:05:00.650
the vast majority of people think

01:05:00.650 --> 01:05:05.453
the vast majority of the
Russian state is highly corrupt.

01:05:07.420 --> 01:05:11.280
And one question is well
why is it so corrupt?

01:05:11.280 --> 01:05:15.510
One obvious answer is a kind
of path dependence story

01:05:15.510 --> 01:05:16.740
that we've talked about,

01:05:16.740 --> 01:05:20.230
that the fact that all
these assets could be seized

01:05:20.230 --> 01:05:23.490
by former Soviet
bureaucrats on the way out,

01:05:23.490 --> 01:05:26.500
or could be extracted
from this very weak state,

01:05:26.500 --> 01:05:31.500
particularly in the 1990s,
is a big part of the story.

01:05:34.340 --> 01:05:38.890
Secondly, there's this
notion of a resource curse,

01:05:38.890 --> 01:05:42.660
which is often called

01:05:45.060 --> 01:05:46.590
the oil curse.

01:05:46.590 --> 01:05:49.833
And here, this is the
political economist's story.

01:05:50.700 --> 01:05:52.690
Now the Russian economy

01:05:54.960 --> 01:05:57.023
at first glance doesn't look like

01:05:57.023 --> 01:06:00.280
it's so completely
dominated by the oil sector.

01:06:00.280 --> 01:06:01.690
You can see here

01:06:03.170 --> 01:06:06.350
at least half of the
Russian economy is services,

01:06:06.350 --> 01:06:11.290
but if you start to look
a little bit more closely

01:06:11.290 --> 01:06:14.860
you see that while there are,

01:06:14.860 --> 01:06:19.860
you know, many different
sectors in the Russian economy,

01:06:20.770 --> 01:06:23.480
one way or another the
vast majority of them

01:06:23.480 --> 01:06:27.090
are connected to the hydrocarbon industry,

01:06:27.090 --> 01:06:29.300
three quarters of the Russian economy.

01:06:29.300 --> 01:06:32.493
So it's very oil dependent.

01:06:33.430 --> 01:06:37.070
You can see, and this
is even more important,

01:06:37.070 --> 01:06:42.070
that the government's revenue
is massively dependent on oil.

01:06:43.950 --> 01:06:48.430
The only countries that
are more oil dependent

01:06:48.430 --> 01:06:51.360
for government revenue are places like

01:06:51.360 --> 01:06:55.653
Saudi Arabia, Iraq, Nigeria, Venezuela.

01:06:57.270 --> 01:07:02.270
The Economist magazine in
2016 estimated that 40%

01:07:02.710 --> 01:07:07.280
of the Russian government's
revenue is from oil.

01:07:07.280 --> 01:07:10.940
And this of course makes
for a lot of corruption

01:07:10.940 --> 01:07:14.730
because if the only way
to get rich in Russia

01:07:14.730 --> 01:07:17.440
is to have access to the oil sector,

01:07:17.440 --> 01:07:20.830
then people who control that access

01:07:20.830 --> 01:07:25.780
can extract huge premiums
for letting you participate.

01:07:25.780 --> 01:07:28.560
